This paper deals with computational geometry and Voronoi diagrams, which are classic topics in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category. The paper also presents approximation algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper discusses graph theory and partitioning, which could place it in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
